<em>Software Configuration
Management Patterns: Effective Teamwork, Practical Integration</em> by
Steve Berczuk with Brad Appleton.

<p>This book describes many of the common problems organizations face
when using SCM in a way that is not consistent with the needs of their
organization. The book presents the patterns organized in a pattern
language that shows how the various structures that you need to use
for an effective SCM system build on each other.
</p>
